# Fix to fix chrome crash on macOS

Step 1: Remove ALL cached drivers (again, clean slate):
rm -rf ~/.wdm

Step 2: Reinstall ChromeDriver cleanly
Run any Selenium test once or run:
python - <<EOF
from webdriver_manager.chrome import ChromeDriverManager
ChromeDriverManager().install()
EOF

Step 3: REMOVE macOS quarantine (MOST IMPORTANT):
xattr -dr com.apple.quarantine ~/.wdm

Step 4: Allow execution explicitly:
chmod +x ~/.wdm/drivers/chromedriver/mac64/*/chromedriver-mac-arm64/chromedriver

Step 5: Validate (must NOT say “killed”):
~/.wdm/drivers/chromedriver/mac64/*/chromedriver-mac-arm64/chromedriver --version
Expected output:
similar to "ChromeDriver 143.0.xxxxx"

Step6: Resume testing.
